amber, clear, heavy cloying sweetness, 
Obviously this is not a traditional beer so if you buy it expecting so, youre gonna have a bad time. This beer has a strong flavor of apple pie and cinnamon. Light body and head. Good dessert beer. Dont think i could drink a more than 1 or 2 though. 4.5%

golden, minimal head, medium bitterness, light body, bitter, 
Not the most exciting or unique beer, but for what it is it works. Very hoppy, crisp, and somewhat light summer lager. Light in color. Light body and smooth 5%

brown, minimal head, clear, medium sweetness, lightly bitter, Toasted coconut flavor medium body, sticky, average carbonation, 
As a fan of brown ales, I really enjoyed Kona Breewerys unique toasted coconut brown ale. Despite the strong aroma and flavor of coconut this beer has a high drinkablity. Its got a great mahogeny color and sweet, nutty flavor. Definitely worth a try!
